title: Fall Out Boy to play Smoothie King Center in March
text:
Fall Out Boy to play Smoothie King Center in March Fall Out Boy to play Smoothie King Center in March Photo provided -- Fall Out Boy ADVOCATE STAFF REPORT Comments 
The multi-platinum-selling Fall Out Boy will perform March 19 at the Smoothie King Center in New Orleans. 
Fall Out Boy’s 20-city “Wintour is Coming” tour will include songs from the group’s sixth studio album, “American Beauty/American Psycho.” The album debuted at No. 1 on the Billboard Top 200 in January 2015. It features the multi-platinum single “Centuries.” The group’s latest single, “Uma Thurman,” is a cross-genre hit charting at Top 5 at Adult Top 40, Top 10 at Pop radio, Top 25 Alternative radio and on Billboard’s Hot 100, Hot Rock, Top 40, AC charts and more. 
Tickets go on sale at 10 a.m. Oct. 16. Full details can be found at www.falloutboy.com . AWOLNATION will open Fall Out Boy’s “Wintour is Coming” shows. Get The Advocate in your inbox
